***************
* Decompile Statement Routine

* Decompiles I-Code to source in I/O buffer

* Passed: I-Code in I-Code Buffer (I.ICBG)
* Return : Decompiled stmt in IOBuff; char cnt in I.IOCT

DCLINE ldy I.ICPT Get icode buf addr
 cmpy I.ICLM
 bhs CPYEOL

* Process Beginning of Line
DCBEG ldb  ,Y Get first token
 cmpb #T.LREF Line number?
 bne DCBEG2
 leay 1,Y Step past it
 lbsr DCLREF Decompile line ref
 lbsr OUTSPC
 ldb  ,Y Get next token
DCBEG2 tst PRTCTL
 bmi DCTOKN No pretty print
 bsr LKTOKE Lookup the token tbl entry
 ldb I.OCNT Get indent count
 pshs B Save global count
 bsr INDCHK Do the indent test
 puls A
 sta I.OCNT Restore global count
 tfr B,A Copy indent count
 lbsr DCLF10 tab over to pretty print field
DCTOKN ldb ,Y+ Restore token
 bmi DCTOK1 Expression member
 bsr LKTOKE Look up token description
 bsr INDCHK Update global pretty print
 bsr PRTOKE Process token
 bra DCTOK2
DCTOK1 lbsr EXPRSN
DCTOK2 cmpy I.ICLM Above icode limit?
 blo DCTOKN ..no; repeat
DCEXIT sty I.ICPT
CPYEOL lda #V$CR Put cr in out buf
 lbra PUTCHR Output eol & return

* Decompile end of line token

DCEOL leas 2,S Throw away return address
 bra DCEXIT All through!

* Subroutine to test token description
*  for Loop structure references.
* Updates local and global indentation counts.

* Passed: A = Descr Byte
*         B = Local Count
* Returns: B = New Local Count, Other Regs Preserved

INDCHK sta ,-S Save descr
 bmi INCHK4 Bra if expr type
 anda #3 Mask fmt bits
 beq INCHK4 Bra if not loop part
 cmpa #1 Top?
 bne INCHK2 Bra if not
 inc I.OCNT Bump global count
 bra INCHK4
INCHK2 decb DECR Local cnt
 bpl INCHK3
 clrb
INCHK3 cmpa #3
 beq INCHK4 Bra if else only
 dec I.OCNT Otherwise decr global
 bpl INCHK4
 clr I.OCNT
INCHK4 lda ,S+ Pop the descr
 rts

***************
* Subr Lktoke
*   Lookup token Description in token table

* Passed: B=Token
* Returns: X=Addr of tbl Entry
*          A=Token Descr Byte From tble

LKTOKE leax DCMTBL,PCR Get tbl addr
 tstb
 bpl LKTOK1
 subb #T.SBYT-T.LBNE-1
LKTOK1 lda #3 3 bytes/entry
 mul
 leax D,X Form addr
 lda ,X Get addr
 rts

***************
* Subr Explod
* Explode I-Code to char

* Looks up token with Lktoke, converts it with Prtoke

* Passed: B=Token
* Returns: Source code in I/O Buffer

EXPLOD bsr LKTOKE Find token entry
* Fall Through to Prtoke

***************
* Subr Prtoke
*    Convert I-Code token to char string.
*    Uses Decompile table data to determine
*    proper decompile action.

* Data in table descriptor (B6:B5) decoded as:
*     x00xxxxx = Pointer to Keyword string
*     x01xxxxx = Relative subroutine offset
*     x10xxxxx = One char literal
*     x11xxxxx = Two char literal

* Passed: A = Descr Byte From Table
*         X = ptr to Table Pack
*         Y = I-Code ptr (Opcode+1)

PRTOKE leax 1,X Move to value part
 anda #$60 Mask code bits
 beq PRTOK1 Bra if keyword str
 cmpa #Z$STSK Keyword+skip?
 bne PRTOK2 Bra if not
 leay 2,Y Skip the line ref
PRTOK1 lda -1,X Get decr again
 pshs A Save it
 ldd ,X Get str addr
 leax D,X Find abs addr
 puls A Restore descr
 anda #$18 Mask fnc bits
 cmpa #$10 is it function?
 beq CPYSTR No spaces if so
 bra SPCSTR Space,string,space

PRTOK2 cmpa #Z$SUB Subroutine entry?
 bne PRTOK3
 ldd  ,X Get the offset
 jmp D,X
PRTOK3 bsr DCLF
 bsr PRTOK4
PRTOK4 lda ,X+ Get the char
 bne PUTCHR Output it

DCLF lda I.IOCT print LF if beyond right "margin"
 cmpa #MARGIN beyond right 'MARGIN'?
 bcs DCLF90 ..no; return carry set
 lda #V$LF
 bsr PUTCHR
 clr I.IOCT reset current position
 tst PRTCTL Pretty printing?
 bmi DCLF90 ..no; done
 lda I.OCNT
 adda #3
DCLF10 asla
 adda #6 add in offset field size
 ldb #V$TAB
 lbsr J$CVIO put spaces in buffer
 clra return carry clear
DCLF90 rts return

