***************
* Subroutine Exprsn
*  Convert I-Code polish expression to string

EXPRSN pshs U Save registers
 ldu <I.OPSP Get icode stack pointer
 clr ,-U Set end of icode stack mark
 clr ,-U
 leay -1,Y Back up to current icode position
EXPRS1 ldb  ,Y Get next icode token
 bpl EXPRS9 Not expression type - exit
 lbsr LKTOKE Look up it's type
 tfr A,B
 lda ,Y+ Get token again
 bitb #Z$GARB Garbage component?
 bne EXPRS1 ..Yes; throw away (garbage)
 orb #$80 Mark operator
 pshu D Push token & type on expr stack
 bitb #Z$OPTR+Z$FREF is it an operator or func ref?
 bne EXPRS1 ..Yes; go get some more
 andb #$7F Mark operand
 pshu D token is an operand - push some extra room
 bitb #Z$LIT is it a literal?
 bne EXPRS2 ..Yes; go handle specially
 ldd ,Y++ Get symtbl ptr
 std 2,U Patch it into expr stack
 bra EXPRS1 Loop until end of expression

* token is a literal
EXPRS2 leay -1,Y
 sty 2,U Save pointer to icode literal
 ldb ,Y+ Get token again
 lbsr NXTTOK Skip literal
 bra EXPRS1

EXPRS9 sty <I.ICPT Update icode pointer
 leay  ,U Set operator stack top
 clra
 clrb
 std ,--Y Set end of operator stack marker
 pshs D Set end of line stack marker
 sta I.CPRC Set old precedence = 0
 sta TEMP Last operator=false
* Fall into Explup

* Y=Optr: Temporary Operator Stack
* U=Expr Stack: Already Full (In Reverse Order)
* S=Line Output Stack
* Destroys A,B,D

EXPLUP ldd ,U++ Pop next token,type
 bitb #Z$OPTR is it an operator?
 beq EXPLU2 ..no; go see what else it might be
 andb #7 Mask precedence
 cmpb I.CPRC is it higher than old precedence?
 bhi EXPLU1 ..Yes; no parens around operands
 bne EXPLU0 If lower, it needs parens
 cmpb #6 Power function?
 bne EXPL05 ..no
 tst TEMP Two power operators in a row?
 beq EXPLU0 ..no; put parens around operands (right to left evaluation)
 bra EXPLU1
EXPL05 tst TEMP Two operators in a row?
 beq EXPLU1 ..no; no parens needed (equal precedence)
EXPLU0 lbsr PARENS Put parenthesis around its operands
EXPLU1 stb I.CPRC Update current precedence
 orb #$80 Remark operator bit
 std ,--Y Push operator on operator stack
 lda #1
 sta TEMP Mark last operator
 bra EXPLUP Loop until done

* This code deals with Operands
EXPLU2 clr TEMP Last operator=false
 bitb #3 Does this thing have any dimensions?
 beq EXPLU5 ..no; go handle a simple variable
 bitb #Z$LIT is it a literal?
 bne EXPLU5 ..Yes; they handle like simple variables
 bitb #Z$FREF is this a function reference?
 bne EXPL25 ..Yes; no SYMPTR entry
 pulu X Pop SYMPTR of variable
 stx ,--Y Push it on operator stack
EXPL25 std ,--Y Push variable token on operator stack
 andb #3 Mask dimensions
 bsr PARENS Put parens around dimensions
 cmpa #T.EOF End of file function?
 bne EXPL27 ..no; continue
 ldx #T.CNUM*256+$FF
 stx ,--Y put channel reference inside parens

EXPL27 ldx #T.COMA*256+$80 Setup comma operator - 0 precedence
 bra EXPLU4
EXPLU3 stx ,--Y Push next comma on operator stack
EXPLU4 decb
 bne EXPLU3 Loop until all commas are accounted for
 stb I.CPRC Erase current precedence for dims (args)
EXPL45 bra EXPLUP Go back for next icode token

* This code handles simple variable & literal Tokens
EXPLU5 bitb #Z$FREF
 bne EXPL55
 pulu X Pull SYMPTR from icode stack
EXPL52 pshs X Put symbol in line stack
EXPL55 pshs D
 cmpa #T.PERD Was that a record reference?
 blo EXPL65
 cmpa #T.P3D
 bls EXPLUP ..Yes; don't pop next operator yet!
EXPL65 ldd ,Y++ Pull operator from opstack
 tstb IS It an operand token?
 bmi EXPLU7 ..no; go do operator stuff
 beq EXPLU8 Bra if end marker
 ldx ,Y++
 bra EXPL52 Loop looking for operator

EXPLU7 pshs D Push operator token on line stack
 clr 1,S Throw away precedence stuff
