* Subroutine REPLACE
*   Replace a part of the I-Code

* Passed: (D)=# Bytes to Delete Before Insertion
*         (Y)=ptr to I-Code
* Returns: (D)=Net Change in I-Code Size
*          (Y)=Updated Past Inserted I-Code
* Destroys: None

* For this routine to work properly, the code to be
* inserted must be located at [I.STBG] thru ICDPTR.
* Also, I.STBG must equal I.ICLM

REPLAC pshs D,X,Y,U Save caller's registers
 leax D,Y Skip over deleted area
 pshs X Save this ptr
 ldy ICDPTR Last byte of inserted code (+1)
 ldd I.STBG
 subd  ,S (d)=length of I-Code following inserted stuff
 beq REPLA1
 lbsr FLOTUP Move new below old I-Code where it goes
REPLA1 ldd ICDPTR
 ldu  ,S First byte to move
 subd ,S++ (d)=number of bytes to move down
 bls REPLA2
 ldy 4,S Original I-Code ptr
 lbsr J$MVDN Accomplish the deletion by moving down
REPLA2 ldd ICDPTR
 subd I.STBG (d)=number of bytes added
 ldy 4,S
 leay D,Y
 sty 4,S Update I-Code ptr past inserted bytes
 subd ,S++ (minus number deleted)
 pshs D Equals the net change in I-Code size
 addd I.ICLM
 std I.ICLM Update I-Code limit
 std I.STBG Update bottom of free space ptr
 ldd G.VARS
 subd  ,S
 std G.VARS Update free space count
 puls D,X,Y,U,PC Return

